+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Reviewed the exported review threads from `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` before making any edits. Classified all five visible threads and limited code/doc changes to the allowed files.
+
+## Thread Classification
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+## Changes Made
+
+### `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+
+- Normalized `approval_state` inside `build_policy_preview(...)` before delegating to `build_preview_payload(...)`.
+
+### `src/policy/preview.py`
+
+- Kept `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in the preview-unavailable fallback payload.
+- Reused a single `requires_human_review` boolean for both preview-enabled and fallback responses.
+
+### `tests/test_preview.py`
+
+- Extended the fallback test to assert `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
+- Added a regression test for `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"` via `build_policy_preview(...)`.
+
+### `docs/approval_policy.md`
+
+- Updated the fallback example to show:
+
+```json
+{
+  "request_id": "req-214",
+  "status": "preview_unavailable",
+  "actor": "review-bot",
+  "approval_state": "human_review_required",
+  "requires_human_review": true
+}
+```
+
+## Verification
+
+Ran:
+
+```bash
+python -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Result:
+
+- `5` tests ran
+- `OK`
+
+## Notes
+
+- `T-214-02` was intentionally left without a separate patch because it duplicates the reopened fallback regression in `T-214-01`.
+- `T-214-03` was intentionally not applied because the review export marks it outdated and the branch instructions explicitly forbid reviving the stale legacy-path idea.
+- No `legacy_preview_hint` field or related alias path was added.
